Ritual Roast – Infrastructure & Deployment Guide

This README describes how to deploy the full Ritual Roast application to AWS using:

Terraform

ECS Fargate

ECR (Docker registry)

RDS MySQL

Secrets Manager

CloudFront + ACM

ALB

GitHub Actions CI/CD

This repo contains both the application code and the IaC (Infrastructure as Code) that powers your production environment.

📁 Project Structure
ritual-roast-code/
├── infra/                     # Terraform modules + environment configs
│   ├── network/               # VPC, subnets, route tables
│   ├── ecs/                   # ECS cluster, tasks, services
│   ├── ecr-ecs.tf             # ECR + ECS task/service
│   ├── rds.tf                 # Database
│   ├── secrets.tf             # Secrets Manager
│   ├── acm-cloudfront.tf      # SSL + CDN
│   ├── alb.tf                 # Load balancer
│   ├── variables.tf
│   └── outputs.tf
│
├── src/                       # App source code (backend/frontend)
├── Dockerfile
└── .github/workflows/
    └── deploy.yml             # CI/CD pipeline for build + deploy

🔧 Requirements

Install these before deploying:

Terraform ≥ 1.6

AWS CLI v2

Docker

Git

GitHub account & repo

AWS IAM user with:

AdministratorAccess (recommended for initial setup)

🔐 Environment Variables for Terraform

Define in a terraform.tfvars file:

Variable	Description
env	Environment name (dev, prod, etc.)
region	AWS region (e.g., us-east-1)
domain	Root domain (yourdomain.com)
hosted_zone_id	Route53 Zone ID
db_username	RDS master username

Example:

env            = "prod"
region         = "us-east-1"
domain         = "ofiliyoungyz.site"
hosted_zone_id = "Z123ABC456XYZ"
db_username    = "ritualadmin"

🔐 Secrets Manager Structure

Terraform automatically creates a secure secret with this JSON schema:

{
  "username": "ritualadmin",
  "password": "GENERATED_STRONG_PASSWORD"
}


Your ECS task pulls them via:

:username::

:password::

Example:

${aws_secretsmanager_secret.db.arn}:username::


Outputs:

terraform output secretsmanager_db_secret_arn

🗄️ RDS – MySQL Database

Terraform provisions:

MySQL 8 RDS instance

Dedicated subnet group

Security groups

Generated password

Private networking

Automated backups

DB endpoint output:

terraform output rds_endpoint

🐳 Docker & ECR

Terraform creates:

ritual-roast (ECR repository)

Manual image push (first-time setup):
aws ecr get-login-password --region <region> \
  | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin <acct>.dkr.ecr.<region>.amazonaws.com

docker build -t ritual-roast .
docker tag ritual-roast:latest <acct>.dkr.ecr.<region>.amazonaws.com/ritual-roast:latest
docker push <acct>.dkr.ecr.<region>.amazonaws.com/ritual-roast:latest

🚀 ECS Fargate Deployment

Terraform deploys:

ECS cluster

Task definition (Fargate)

Service (desired_count = 2)

Load balancer

CloudWatch logs

Secure networking in private subnets

Your app receives:

DB credentials from Secrets Manager (JSON keys)

Environment variables (DB_HOST, DB_NAME, AWS_REGION)

ECR image URL

ECS service auto-redeploys when GitHub Actions pushes a new image.

🌍 CloudFront + HTTPS

Terraform configures:

ACM SSL certificate (validated via DNS)

CloudFront distribution

ALB as origin

Route53 or Namecheap DNS

If using Namecheap, add this CNAME:

terraform output acm_dns_validation_cname

🤖 CI/CD – GitHub Actions

Workflow location:

.github/workflows/deploy.yml


Pipeline tasks:

Authenticate to AWS

Build Docker image

Push image to ECR

Update ECS service

(Optional) terraform apply

Required GitHub Secrets:
Secret Name	Purpose
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID	AWS IAM auth
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY	AWS IAM auth
AWS_REGION	Region
AWS_ACCOUNT_ID	ECR push
ECR_REPO_NAME	ritual-roast
DOMAIN	App domain
HOSTED_ZONE_ID	DNS setup
▶️ Deployment Steps
1. Initialize Terraform
terraform init

2. Validate
terraform validate

3. Plan
terraform plan

4. Deploy
terraform apply -auto-approve

5. Push Docker Image

Either done manually or by GitHub Actions.

6. Visit Production URL 🎉
https://<your-domain>

🧪 Troubleshooting
❌ ECS task failing to start

Check CloudWatch Logs → incorrect secret path:

Correct format:

<secret arn>:username::
<secret arn>:password::

❌ "Cannot pull image"

Fix: your execution role must include:

AmazonECSTaskExecutionRolePolicy

secretsmanager:GetSecretValue

ecr:GetAuthorizationToken

❌ ACM certificate stuck "Pending validation"

Add DNS CNAME exactly as Terraform printed.

